Commentary: back of a length outside off, rides the bounce and clubs this through midwicket! Belting start, Curran gives chase but it's agonisingly out of reach, and he can drag it back in with a despairing dive
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: length outside off, driven to cover on the edge of the ring. 86mph/138kph
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: hard length on fourth stump, clipped to straight midwicket. 86mph/138kph

struck on the pad, big appeal but not given. Up at 87mph/141kph. England won't review it. Hard length, pitched outside leg and skidded on quickly, striking Fakhar on the pad as he looked to work to leg
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: length ball, clipped into the leg side. 88mph/141kph
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: banged in on a hard length again, Fakhar is cramped for room and can't get it away
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: short outside off, rocks back and hammers this out to deep midwicket
skids on with the angle, clipped into the leg side for a scurried single
length ball, clipped out to wide long-on and they scamper back for two. Great running!
length outside off, pushed out to Jordan at wide long-on, no second run this time

length ball on fourth stump, rocks back and steers this elegantly through backward point for four! No real turn, piercing the gap between point and third man. Opens the face, and this outfield is quick
Commentary_short: Ali to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: skips down the wicket, heaving this down to long-on via the inside edge

looks for a yorker wide of the off stump to start, down at 83mph, and Fakhar squeezes this out through extra cover for four! Billings, who is quick, gives chase, but won't cut it off. Turned into a low full toss - a freebie for Fakhar
Commentary_short: Jordan to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: length in the channel, guided to point. 82mph/132kph
Commentary_short: Jordan to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: offcutter down at 67mph/109kph, clipped towards midwicket for one
hard length outside off, cut away wide of Rashid at third man and Babar races back for the second
cutter on the hip, clipped out to Billings at deep square who races in to prevent any chance of the second
slower ball again, drags a pull out to the legside sweeper
slower ball to start outside off, 70mph/113kph, and carved out to deep cover
another 70mph slower ball which completely foxes Babar, who is through the shot far too early and struck high on the back thigh. Made to look foolish!
Commentary_short: Curran to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: speared down the leg side at 80mph/128kph, called a wide a no-ball in fact, via the Finn Rule as he knocked the bails off at the non-striker's end in his delivery stride
Commentary_short: Curran to Babar Azam, 1 no ball

Commentary: slower ball out the back of the hand on a length outside off, clothed to extra cover on the bounce
Commentary_short: Curran to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: jams in a straight yorker, which Babar digs out to straight midwicket in the ring
Commentary_short: Curran to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: nope, bluff from Curran who goes slightly full of a length on off stump. Babar clips it away off the pads to get off strike

slower ball, banged in on a length at 73mph/117kph, which Fakhar pulls behind square... and it dribbles away for four! Dragged the pull past short fine leg on the 45-degree angle, and had enough on it to beat the boundary-rider
Commentary_short: Curran to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: short, wide, cut away for four! Another loose ball to start from Jordan, like his first over, and Babar frees his arms to flay this to the point boundary
Commentary_short: Jordan to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower ball in the channel, completely bamboozles him. 68mph, and Babar is through the shot early looking to force it through the off side
Commentary_short: Jordan to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: slower ball again, picks it this time and pulls out into the leg side for one
full on off stump, Fakhar clears the front leg and whacks this dead-straight past Jordan down the ground for four! Checked drive, high front elbow, and races away
Commentary_short: Jordan to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: pulled to Rashid in the circle on the 45-degree angle, Babar scrambles through for a single and the throw is wide
slower ball outside off, guided down to third man on the rope with a steered cut
full and straight, whipped straight to short midwicket
Commentary_short: Curran to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: quicker ball, drops his hands and steers to backward point for one
short ball which takes Fakhar by surprise! He opens the face, and steers this over the vacant slip cordon for four via the shoulder of the bat. Not sure he knew too much about that one
Commentary_short: Curran to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower ball on a length, punched out to deep cover
clipped off the pads to deep backward square, big dive from Banton but they ease back for two
full toss on leg stump, very loose ball, but only clipped out to Banton at deep square again. Curran escapes!
full on leg stump to start, big appeal from Bairstow behind the stumps but Saggers isn't interested and nor is Eoin Morgan. Sliding down, I think
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: tossed up outside leg, clipped behind square for an early single
full on fifth stump, driven firmly out to long-off
huge legbreak which rips past the bat! Magic ball, enormous turn past Babar's outside edge and he does well to keep his back foot down as Bairstow whips the bails off
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: legbreak, too short though and Babar rocks back to nail this through midwicket for four! Stayed low off the pitch, so Babar had to wait and drag this in front of square, beating the man at cow corner
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: clipped into the leg side, Billings races in from the fence to prevent the second
nothing ball outside off which Babar nails over mid-off for four! Freebie to start, offcutter in the channel but right in the slot and Babar isn't missing out on that
Commentary_short: Gregory to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: full on the pads, clipped down to deep backward square. Rashid does well to save the second
offcutter into the pitch, pulled awkwardly down to long-on
pace on, 82mph/132kph, and driven to mid-off
Commentary_short: Gregory to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: slower ball, full on fourth stump, clipped out to Jordan at deep midwicket
offcutter on a length, pulled into the body and it dribbles away into the off side. Decent recovery from Gregory after a loose start
booooom! Towering six over midwicket! Googly from Rashid which pitches in the slot outside the leg stump. Fakhar clears the front leg and mooses this over the rope - nearly out of the ground, in fact
Commentary_short: Rashid to Fakhar Zaman, SIX runs

Commentary: nudged into the leg side, think about the single but Rashid gets round well off his own bowling
Commentary_short: Rashid to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: pushed wider outside the off stump, out the front of the hand, pulled miiiiiiles up into the air and Banton runs in from the long-on boundary to pouch it! England finally get a breakthrough, Banton clinging onto the high ball. Pushed through a little quicker from Rashid, up at 57mph, and Fakhar didn't quite get the connection he was after
Dismissal_text: Fakhar Zaman c Banton b Rashid 36 (38m 22b 5x4 1x6) SR: 163.63

Commentary: drags a pull out to deep midwicket
flat legbreak, drops short, but Hafeez can't beat the man in the deep
full on leg stump, dug out into the leg side as Billings fields. Fumbles the one-handed pick-up, but ran in quickly enough to dissuade them from running two
hard length outside off, class shot down to third man for four! Mahmood was fielding quite wide, so Babar jammed his bat down late, dabbing through the vacant slip cordon and away to the fence
Commentary_short: Gregory to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: pace on again, clipped into the leg side
84mph/135kph length ball, tucked out to deep midwicket
cutter outside off, steered down to third man with an open face

offcutter, Hafeez doesn't pick it and is through the pull shot early but gets enough of a tickle on it, and it races away past Bairstow's despairing dive. <strike>Given as runs</strike>, but looked like it just came off his hip. EDIT: Scratch that, given as leg-byes. As you were!
Commentary_short: Gregory to Mohammad Hafeez, 4 leg byes

Commentary: hard length, pulled out to midwicket to keep the strike
tossed up outside off and spinning away, cut for one off the back foot
cracked through midwicket! Goes back and gets hold of Rashid, hammers this on the pull
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: stroked through extra, this is going to beat the man out! Despairing dive on the rope but he won't get there - brings up Azam's fifty, the Pakistan captain leading from the front
Commentary_short: Rashid to Babar Azam, FOUR runs

Commentary: flicked into the leg side for one
ugghh, big full toss outside off, Hafeez isn't quite sure what to do with it and nearly slaps it to deep point
lobbed up on the stumps, worked down the ground
short outside off, Azam goes back and angles the ball for one to third man
crunched over deep square leg! The old dog collars this, just a breezy swing at short ball on off and he carts it up and over for six!
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX runs

Commentary: dug in again, wide of off and Hafeez again pulls, splices it up and over midwicket for one
shortish outside off, cut through point to the sweeper
bumper, gets this up above the shoulder, Hafeez swings to leg and gets it off the gloves behind square
short, 77mph/126kph outside off and Azam cuts to backward point, they won't get one there
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Babar Azam, no run

Commentary: another full toss, Hafeez has to try and drag it from wide of off, slugs one to long-on
legbreak, straightening on middle and leg, Azam rocks back and hauls him through midwicket
drops a little short, Hafeez swats it between deep midwicket and long-on, Jordan keeps them to one

Babar holes out! Frustration etched on his face, the ball was dragged down, but he succeeded only in clubbing it down the throat of deep midwicket! Just when Pakistan would have been looking for him to launch... Rashid strikes again
Dismissal_text: Babar Azam c Billings b Rashid 56 (55m 44b 7x4 0x6) SR: 127.27

Commentary: slips in the googly, coming back in as Malik goes back and cuts
Commentary_short: Rashid to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: lobs up the legbreak, swatted down the ground to get off the mark
fullish down the leg side, that's a wide to begin with
fired on a length, coming back on off and chopped into the ground towards backward point
in the channel, possibly a cutter and Malik attempts to drive, gets it off the inside half of the bat and Gregory hares after it
Commentary_short: Gregory to Shoaib Malik, no run

Commentary: shortish outside off, dabbed down to third man
plinked over mid-on, just enough on it to clear the man running back
slower ball, cut away but finds the man at backward point
Commentary_short: Gregory to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: goes wide of off stump, Hafeez attempts to exploit that fielding change by scooping leg side, but can't lay bat on another cutter
Commentary_short: Gregory to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: short and at the ribs, Malik is tucked up on the back foot, worked to leg
back of a length, tonked straight down the ground! Hafeez opens up his stance and baseball-bats it back over the bowler's head for a welcome four!
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: short ball skidding on, swung into the leg side
steepling bouncer, that's too high for the umpires
short over the top of off stump, worked towards midwicket
smashes down the ground again! Hafeez sits back and smokes Mahmood over mid-off and away
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: angled in and flipped leg side
slower ball and flicked to the leg side

sliced behind point, Malik wants a second, could be tight... but Bairstow hasn't collected the ball cleanly! Malik looked to be struggling as Billings fired in the throw, but the keeper wasn't in control as he broke the stumps. And they stole an extra run, too as the ball rolled away
clatters a high full toss over deep backward square! Latches on and kerplunks this into the stands! That's a no-ball, to increase Curran's pain
Commentary_short: Curran to Mohammad Hafeez, (no ball) SIX runs

Commentary: smoked over the off side! Picked the slower ball and climbed into it on the drive, races away. Tough start for Curran
Commentary_short: Curran to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: short, flipped over backward square leg
fires in a full-pace yorker wide of off, jams down on it towards backward point for one
pace off, 67mph but Hafeez is waiting, banged over the rope at deep square! Pulled hard and flat and that fetches him six more, Hafeez is flying now
Commentary_short: Curran to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX runs

Commentary: slotted down the ground! Full outside off and it's basically a half-volley, Malik steps out and lofts it over mid-off and away
Commentary_short: Jordan to Shoaib Malik, FOUR runs

Commentary: short, tennis-ball bounce, high and leg side - one more to the extra column
low full toss, Malik is across and whips a couple towards deep midwicket, that's the 50 stand up, from just 26 balls

blasts it straight to extra cover! Jordan misses the yorker but gets the wicket... Malik was looking to do as he did first ball of the over and chip down the ground, but managed to slice this slightly, Morgan leaping to take a good catch high to his right
Dismissal_text: Shoaib Malik c Morgan b Jordan 14 (23m 11b 1x4 0x6) SR: 127.27

Commentary: pitched up and dinked down the ground to long-on
slower ball, Hafeez is across his stumps, worked away to the leg side
spears in the yorker, dug out down to long-on
length outside off, it's another cutter and Iftikhar slices it down to third man swinging hard
scooped over short fine leg! Coolly done, just a half step and flicks the full toss, deep backward square leg won't get around - fifty for Hafeez, who won't be put in the corner, no sir
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: belted down the ground! Length outside off and Hafeez makes room to slap it over mid-off, picks up another boundary
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Mohammad Hafeez, FOUR runs

Commentary: fuller, outside off and he mistimes this, dragged into the leg side

pitched up, not quite yorker length and Iftikhar heaves across the line, deflects it back to the bowler... they are going to check whether the ball came straight off his boot, before Mahmood caught it. But no, definitely went into the ground
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Iftikhar Ahmed, no run

Commentary: speared in full, Mahmood goes up for lbw, nearly rolls on to the stumps anyway... then Bairstow throws down the non-striker's end! Was Iftikhar ball-watching? He had to get his skates on after Hafeez called him through, they then stole another as the ball ran away. In fact, England reviewed for lbw, which was a terrible call, as it pretty much hit him outside leg stump; and Iftikhar was just in at the other end, too! So a lot of sound and fury signifying nothing two leg byes
Commentary_short: Mahmood to Iftikhar Ahmed, 2 leg byes

Commentary: offcutter, on a length outside off, whumped over cow corner! Hafeez ab-so-lutely bazookas this into the stands, feet planted and swiped imperiously over the leg side for six more!
Commentary_short: Jordan to Mohammad Hafeez, SIX runs

Commentary: fires in the yorker, Jordan fields in his follow through and then has a shy with Hafeez advancing out of his ground, he has to throw himself for the crease
Commentary_short: Jordan to Mohammad Hafeez, no run

Commentary: full bunger on middle and leg, 88mph/141kph and he can only bunt one down to long-on
another 88mph/141kph yorker on leg, Iftikhar can't do much and it trickles into the leg side for one
full and whipped leg side, in front of Billings at deep midwicket and they'll come back for two
dropped! Full, 88mph and in the slot, driven uppishly and Morgan cant cling on this time! Made a good effort, one-handed going to his left, Hafeez sliced it high and just got away with it
full toss, can't get under it as Hafeez swings one to deep midwicket
pitched up, 81mph/130kph and Iftikhar heaves wide of long-on for a couple
86mph/138kph full toss, swung away leg side, not a great connection and they only get one to deep backward square
another low full toss, swivelled away through backward square leg, Gregory does well to prevent it going for four

plinked to cover, Morgan takes a simple catch and Hafeez is done for! Maybe a slower ball from Curran, got right underneath it and barely travelled beyond the edge of the ring... but still been a cracking knock from Le Prof
Dismissal_text: Mohammad Hafeez c Morgan b Curran 69 (63m 36b 5x4 4x6) SR: 191.66

Commentary: back-of-the-hand slowie, wide of the stumps and Iftikhar can only swipe it to backward point for one to finish
length outside off, can't beat short cover
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Banton, no run

Commentary: skids on from very wide on the crease, clipped down to long-on to get up and running
nudges to square leg and sets off for a quick single
speared in at 63mph/101kph on a length, tickled behind square on the leg side for a scrambled single
skiddy length ball, nudged to wide mid-on on the back foot. 65mph
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Bairstow, no run

Commentary: skids on with the angle again, nudged to that same man
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Bairstow, no run

Commentary: hard length, hurries Banton for pace and cramps him for room as he bottom-edges it down to fine leg in the ring. 85mph/137kph to start
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, 1 run

Commentary: length ball pushed across him, inside-edges towards midwicket looking to drive
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, no run

Commentary: full on fourth stump, Bairstow throws his hands at it and heaves through wide mid-on! Wristy whip with the bottom hand choking the bat, and it flies away to the rope
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, FOUR runs

Commentary: wide outside the off stump, plinked just over extra cover in close and away for four! Hafeez was there, five yards in from the edge of the ring, but he couldn't quite get a hand on it leaping back
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, FOUR runs

Commentary: leg-stump yorker, Rizwan and Shaheen go up for the lbw but it's not given. Babar shouts 'shabash, shabash!' but won't send it upstairs, might have pitched outside leg? Yep, just outside, I reckon
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, 1 run

Commentary: full and straight, clipped to straight midwicket and Banton sets off for a sharp single
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, 1 run

Commentary: oh my goodness, Tom Banton you are a freak! Imad has tied England down so well in this series, so Banton swaps round and reverse-sweeps this for six over third man! Shot boy! Clears the rope with ease
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Banton, SIX runs

Commentary: heaves into the leg side through midwicket for a couple more
Banton gives himself room, Imad follows him and is clipped to mid-on for a sharp single
gets his weight across to the off side, lap-sweeping behind square for four more! Raced away into the vacant long leg region, Bairstow got down early and timed this nicely
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Bairstow, FOUR runs

Commentary: skids on with the angle, Bairstow tucks out to deep square for one

length on off stump, heaved into the leg side... and it falls into no-man's-land. Babar was running back from inside the ring but couldn't quite get back underneath it. Premeditates the slog-sweep, no timing but gets away with it
slower ball to start, length on the pads and tickled fine for four! Freebie for Bairstow to start, worked away off the hip and it runs away. England flying
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Banton, FOUR runs

Commentary: length on leg stump, Bairstow frees his arms and short-arm jabs this over long leg for six! Horrible start for Amir, too straight, and Bairstow cashes in
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Bairstow, SIX runs

Commentary: slower ball, banged in as Bairstow gives himself room, steering straight to point in the ring
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Bairstow, no run

Commentary: slower ball pushed across him, dabbed to backward point
slightly full of a length, clipped into the leg side and they scramble through for one. Amir fields off his own bowling but Banton was safely in
slower ball into the pitch, clipped out to deep square for one
full slower ball, dug out into the covers. 75mph/120kph, pushed down across the side of the ball
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, 1 run

Commentary: backs away, giving himself room, and Afridi digs a slower-ball bouncer in halfway down. Banton waits for it, and carves into the covers
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, 1 run

Commentary: length ball, heaved out to deep square with strong bottom hand
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, 1 run

Commentary: offcutter, clipped into the leg side
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Banton, 1 run

Commentary: full toss outside off stump, plinked over mid-on's head and plugs in the outfield. Called a no-ball for height
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, (no ball) 2 runs

Commentary: length outside off, Bairstow heaves out towards midwicket but his bat skewed in his hand and it plugs in the outfield. Just a couple
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, 2 runs

Commentary: struck on the pad, Afridi belts out an appeal but not sure this had much going for it - sounded like bat first, and might even have pitched outside leg. Babar doesn't fancy the review
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Bairstow, 1 leg bye

Commentary: length in the off-stump channel, Bairstow frees his arms and nails this over square midwicket for six! Pulled hard, not much elevation but plenty of distance
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Bairstow, SIX runs

Commentary: hard length on off stump, opens the face to steal a single behind square on the off side
slower ball pushed across the right-handed batsman, and Banton only connects with thin air
Commentary_short: Mohammad Amir to Banton, no run

Commentary: length on the pads, tucked out to deep midwicket for one
slashed away, half-stopped at point by the diving Shadab. Good work to save two runs
length outside off, Bairstow frees his arms to whack this through the covers but the man gets round to cut it off
legbreak, punched out to deep cover

full and straight, swept high, high, HIGH into the air and pouched at square leg! Shadab Khan makes the breakthrough, Imad clinging onto the chance, and Shadab roars in celebration. Full legbreak, pushed through, and top-edged miles into the air as Bairstow got down to sweep
Dismissal_text: JM Bairstow c Imad Wasim b Shadab Khan 44 (34m 24b 4x4 2x6) SR: 183.33

Commentary: Banton gets down to sweep, he's struck on the pad and given! Banton reviews but this looked good to the naked eye. Looked like the googly, Banton got down to slog-sweep but was slightly late on the shot. No bat involved, was the impact in line? Umpire's call on impact, hitting middle stump three-quarters of the way up, and Saggers can stick with his original decision. Shadab gets two in two!
Dismissal_text: T Banton lbw b Shadab Khan 20 (37m 16b 0x4 1x6) SR: 125.00

Commentary: legbreak, steered towards point with an open face. Malan thinks about a single but Morgan barks 'NO!'
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morgan, no run

Commentary: legbreak, struck on the pad, loud appeal from Shadab and Babar reviews after Saggers says no. Looked like it might have taken the inside edge on first viewing, but Ultra-Edge says no bat involved. This will be tight... oosh, umpire's call on impact! Very close, smashing the top of middle, but Morgan survives
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morgan, no run

Commentary: flat legbreak, Morgan rocks onto the back foot and pulls out to long-on
nudged into the covers to get off strike
floaty ball on leg stump which goes on with the arm, Malan defends with soft hands
Commentary_short: Iftikhar Ahmed to Malan, no run

Commentary: speared in with a round-arm action, Malan drops back in the crease, opening the face to run this away past third man's right hand in the ring and away for four. Classy shot
Commentary_short: Iftikhar Ahmed to Malan, FOUR runs

Commentary: fired through on a length, clipped out to deep midwicket
length, wide outside off. Morgan nails the cut in front of square but can't beat short cover
Commentary_short: Iftikhar Ahmed to Morgan, no run

Commentary: clipped off the pads out to straight midwicket, instantly looking for two, but the fielder races in off the rope to dissuade them
bosh, slog-swept for a towering six! Googly, pitching on leg and turning onto middle, but Morgan picked it out of the hand and nailed it over square leg
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morgan, SIX runs

Commentary: googly on a length outside off, cut firmly out towards deep point
flat on leg stump, clipped out to cow corner to give Malan the strike
legbreak, chipped back to the bowler but just short! Diving forward and to his right, but soft enough hands to fall in from of the hands
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Malan, no run

Commentary: nudged away to get off strike
whacked dead-straight over Shadab's head for four! Morgan is up and running here - tossed up on the stumps, and bludgeoned over umpire Saggers' right shoulder as he ducked for cover
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: smeared in at the pads as Malan gives himself room, punching out to long-off
round-arm action, Morgan opens up, giving himself room to force out to deep extra cover
skids on with the angle, pressed straight to short extra in the ring
Commentary_short: Iftikhar Ahmed to Morgan, no run

Commentary: length on the pads, clipped deftly towards midwicket and they set off for a sharp single as Rizwan gives chase
skids on from round the wicket, pushed out to long-on
length in the channel, hammered out to long-off to keep the strike
back of a length over off stump, stabbed through the covers for one
shortish on leg stump, 85mph/137kph and Malan is happy to shovel it away through backward square leg
full, think that was a cutter, too, right up in the blockhole and dug out for one
fullish outside off and drilled through the covers
gets the yorker in, 88mph/141kph on off and Morgan can only bunt towards mid-off for another single
91mph/147kph, back of a length, Malan swishes at it and thick-edges into his thigh pad - dot ball, and that's a superb over from Rauf
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Malan, no run

Commentary: spanked over long-off! Sat up outside off, Morgan waited for it, heaved a flat, straight jab through the line for six!
Commentary_short: Iftikhar Ahmed to Morgan, SIX runs

Commentary: quicker on the stumps, whipped away to long-on
flat on middle, Malan steps away and exposes his stumps, slashed through point for four! Belted to the rope
Commentary_short: Iftikhar Ahmed to Malan, FOUR runs

Commentary: pushed through and again there's width for Malan, he cuts powerfully but deep cover gets around to this one
flicked through midwicket playing back
cut behind point and he gets it through! Morgan making room and he breaks the wrists on a late dab for four... Ifti's figures take a hit as England bounce back
Commentary_short: Iftikhar Ahmed to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: on the stumps, slugged back down the ground to long-on
blootered into the stands at deep backward square! That was a cutter, I think, but he picked it and swished up and over, in his arc and that's a lovely connection
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Morgan, SIX runs

Commentary: spears this full, 91mph/147kph outside off and Morgan fails to get under it, chopped to cover
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Morgan, no run

Commentary: another cutter, half-volley wide of off stump, mistimed through mid-on for one
length ball, Malan sets his feet and clubs to deep midwicket for one more
smeared over extra cover! Full toss and Morgan rifles it for four more! England take 13 off the over
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: over the wicket, tossed up and worked through midwicket
Morgan is across his stumps to sweep, gets it fine but well stopped on the edge of the ring
pushed through outside off, Malan cuts for one through backward point
quicker, maybe the wrong'un and it kicks up, Morgan jumps and jabs it back through mid-on
smoked over the leg side! Malan plants the front foot, hits with the spin and gets it all the way over the long boundary for six!
Commentary_short: Shadab Khan to Malan, SIX runs

Commentary: spins down the leg side, that'll help England
floated up and worked off the pads
full, 87mph/139kph, tailing in and Malan drives, gets one to extra cover
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, 1 run

Commentary: goes for the edge of the tramlines... tight call, think Jofra Archer in the World Cup final Super Over, but Martin Saggers signals wide
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, 1 wide

Commentary: in the arc, out of the park! Morgan unleashes a trademark slog-sweep off the fast bowler, low full toss and he's belted almost out of the ground at deep square! Fifty for England's captain, and he looks to be taking his side home here
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, SIX runs

Commentary: full outside off, Morgan chops down on it, sets off for one anyway... and has to dive for his ground as Shaheen toe-pokes wide of the stumps in his follow through! Would have been tight, think Morgan was back
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, no run

Commentary: short, swivels on the pull, sends it skittering away through backward square! Uses the pace on the ball and beats the man in the deep leg side
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: full, comes out as a half-volley, creamed up and over extra! Runs coming in a flood for England now, Azam can't plug the gaps
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: low full toss, thick-edged past the keeper for four more! Sums up Pakistan's fortunes in the last few overs, pace on and he just gets something on it, racing away to the rope. Predictor at 96% for England
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Morgan, FOUR runs

Commentary: round the wicket, flat trajectory on off and Malan mishits it back to the bowler
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Malan, no run

Commentary: looped up, opens up and strokes one through the covers
tossed up, Morgan waits on it, opens the face really late and runs one to short third man
flat and quick and carved though point! Uses the pace on the ball from Imad and belts a cut
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Malan, FOUR runs

Commentary: eased up and over extra cover now! Malan steps out and lofts this to the rope, England bringing the target in sight
Commentary_short: Imad Wasim to Malan, FOUR runs

Commentary: goes over the wicket, nudged off the pads to leg for one
slapped through midwicket on the pull! Short ball, 82mph/132kph and Malan swings it away nonchalantly
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Malan, FOUR runs

Commentary: slower ball, I think, on leg stump and Malan fails to connect slogging across the line
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Malan, no run

Commentary: length, pace off and it foxes Malan, spinning and skipping through outside off, doesn't even play a shot
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Malan, no run

Commentary: pitched up and swatted down the ground to long-on

picks out deep backward square! Is that the wicket that sparks Pakistan? Swings for the hills but doesn't quite get hold of this one... Straight down the gullet of the man in the deep. Morgan hasn't quite finished the job, but it's been a sparkling knock
Dismissal_text: EJG Morgan c sub (Khushdil Shah) b Haris Rauf 66 (45m 33b 6x4 4x6) SR: 200.00

Commentary: good length, beats the bat outside off as Malan hangs in the crease
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Malan, no run

Commentary: launched over the off side... plugs short of the man on the rope
dragged down, Malan rocks back and swats a pull between deep midwicket and long-on for a couple, Moeen racing back to the danger end
tossed up and Malan attempts to reverse-sweep, cue-ends it for one

half-tracker, plinked to midwicket! Another one goes, Shadab picks up his third wicket... Just a woeful mishit from Moeen, rocking back and skewing it tamely to the man inside the ring. Alarm bells ringing for England yet??
Dismissal_text: MM Ali c Babar Azam b Shadab Khan 1 (5m 2b 0x4 0x6) SR: 50.00

Commentary: flighted, full outside off and Billing drags it down to long-off
pushes through the legbreak and Malan nudges one into the covers to keep the strike
pitched up outside off and Malan strokes through cover point on the front foot
91mph/147kph, full in the slot, dug out through midwicket
attempted yorker, 92mph/148kph on the stumps, Malan calmly steps away and punches through the off side
scooped for four! Billings is across his stumps takes the short ball up and over to fine leg
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Billings, FOUR runs

Commentary: clobbered down the ground! Billings drops back, turns the yorker into a half-volley and smokes it back past the bowler - England need one to win!
Commentary_short: Haris Rauf to Billings, FOUR runs

Commentary: picks out backward point! Billings won't be finishing it, he's picked out the man for a simple catch - off the toe of the bat, but not much of a celebration from Rauf. Pakistan need something miraculous from here
Dismissal_text: SW Billings c Fakhar Zaman b Haris Rauf 10 (8m 5b 2x4 0x6) SR: 200.00

Commentary: full outside off, Malan bunts it through the infield, England win by five wickets!
Commentary_short: Shaheen Shah Afridi to Malan, FOUR runs
